WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.003
[phone plays ditzy pop song. buzzing]

2
00:00:07.174 --> 00:00:09.176
[Paula breathing heavily]

3
00:00:10.552 --> 00:00:11.887
[phone stops playing]

4
00:00:16.058 --> 00:00:17.851
[phone buzzes. playing song]

5
00:00:21.063 --> 00:00:23.065
[tense music plays]

6
00:00:25.359 --> 00:00:26.360
[phone stops]

7
00:00:30.280 --> 00:00:32.281
[phone buzzes. playing song]

8
00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:40.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

9
00:00:43.168 --> 00:00:44.336
[chimes. buzzes]

10
00:00:46.380 --> 00:00:48.507
[phone buzzes. playing song]

11
00:01:38.182 --> 00:01:39.808
[children chattering]

12
00:01:41.351 --> 00:01:43.687
- [Gwynn] Oh. thank you.
- Sure. Okay. All right.

13
00:01:44.271 --> 00:01:45.355
Outfit change?

14
00:01:45.939 --> 00:01:47.941
[children laughing. chattering]

15
00:01:56.867 --> 00:01:59.077
[panting]

16
00:02:01.163 --> 00:02:03.081
- [knocks on door]
- [Gwynn] Paula?

17
00:02:04.249 --> 00:02:07.168
- [knocking continues]
- Hey. Paula. We're leaving.

18
00:02:07.169 --> 00:02:09.085
I'll see you at the fundraiser tomorrow. right?

19
00:02:09.086 --> 00:02:10.421
And-And I borrowed a ziplock.

20
00:02:10.422 --> 00:02:12.591
Great. Enjoy.

21
00:02:17.221 --> 00:02:18.638
[ominous music playing]

22
00:02:18.639 --> 00:02:21.225
[phone ringing]

23
00:02:28.315 --> 00:02:29.316
[groans]

24
00:02:31.485 --> 00:02:32.568
[Geri] <i>Hello</i>.

25
00:02:32.569 --> 00:02:34.070
Prepare to be thrilled and delighted

26
00:02:34.071 --> 00:02:35.488
because we pulled off
the coup of the century.

27
00:02:35.489 --> 00:02:37.657
- We got the killer's number.
- I was gonna say that.

28
00:02:37.658 --> 00:02:39.659
[Geri] <i>Yeah. but we-we found
that woman's phone</i>

29
00:02:39.660 --> 00:02:41.536
<i>and it didn't even have a password on it.</i>

30
00:02:41.537 --> 00:02:43.746
<i>So we got the killer's number
and now we can track him down.</i>

31
00:02:43.747 --> 00:02:45.081
He's dead. He's dead.

32
00:02:45.082 --> 00:02:47.917
- [inhales sharply] I killed him.
- What?

33
00:02:47.918 --> 00:02:50.795
I. uh… [chuckles] …he tried to attack me

34
00:02:50.796 --> 00:02:54.549
and-and-and-and he tried to kill me.
and so I-I…

35
00:02:54.550 --> 00:02:58.010
[stammers] Uh. I shot him in the face.

36
00:02:58.011 --> 00:02:59.428
- [whimpers]
- [Rudy] <i>You have a gun?</i>

37
00:02:59.429 --> 00:03:02.056
[whimpering] Fuck.

38
00:03:02.057 --> 00:03:05.101
Fuck. Fuck. fuck. [whimpers]

39
00:03:05.102 --> 00:03:06.895
Okay. uh. what did the police say?

40
00:03:07.479 --> 00:03:08.604
[panting]

41
00:03:08.605 --> 00:03:09.606
[Geri] <i>Paula?</i>

42
00:03:10.607 --> 00:03:12.817
Okay. uh. Paula. listen to me.

43
00:03:12.818 --> 00:03:14.945
Um. uh. what did the police say?

44
00:03:16.613 --> 00:03:17.697
<i>Paula?</i>

45
00:03:17.698 --> 00:03:20.032
I didn't... I didn't call the police.

46
00:03:20.033 --> 00:03:21.242
I ran away.

47
00:03:21.243 --> 00:03:24.287
Oh. my God.
I took his phone and I ran away.

48
00:03:24.288 --> 00:03:25.580
- [Geri] <i>You what?</i>
- Yeah.

49
00:03:25.581 --> 00:03:26.582
[knocks on door]

50
00:03:27.958 --> 00:03:29.251
Mom.

51
00:03:30.085 --> 00:03:31.086
Coming.

52
00:03:32.629 --> 00:03:34.964
Where's Shmooey?
I can't go to Prem's house without her.

53
00:03:34.965 --> 00:03:38.759
Oh. no. Okay.
Uh. I'll... I'll find her. Um…

54
00:03:38.760 --> 00:03:40.344
[Rudy] <i>Pau… Paula. listen to me.</i>

55
00:03:40.345 --> 00:03:42.973
<i>You need to put the phone back
and call the police.</i>

56
00:03:44.057 --> 00:03:45.766
Yeah. I can't. [clears throat]

57
00:03:45.767 --> 00:03:47.185
Paula. you're in shock.

58
00:03:47.186 --> 00:03:48.728
You're-You're not thinking straight.

59
00:03:48.729 --> 00:03:52.690
So. Rudy is right. which I never say.
and you need to go back now.

60
00:03:52.691 --> 00:03:54.525
Bye. Bye. bye. bye. bye. bye.

61
00:03:54.526 --> 00:03:56.736
See you. Bye. Okay.

62
00:03:56.737 --> 00:03:57.987
[Geri] <i>It was self-defense. okay?</i>

63
00:03:57.988 --> 00:04:00.281
<i>So just go put the phone back
and call 911…</i>

64
00:04:00.282 --> 00:04:02.491
- They're waiting for me.
- <i>…and the police will figure it out.</i>

65
00:04:02.492 --> 00:04:04.327
Yeah. Okay. okay. I will.

66
00:04:04.328 --> 00:04:05.661
Just let me think.

67
00:04:05.662 --> 00:04:06.746
No thinking necessary.

68
00:04:06.747 --> 00:04:08.748
We're on our way. Say you'll do it.

69
00:04:08.749 --> 00:04:10.291
Mom. they're waiting on me.

70
00:04:10.292 --> 00:04:12.503
[Geri] <i>Tell me you'll take the phone back
and call the police.</i>

71
00:04:13.837 --> 00:04:16.339
- <i>Paula. say you'll do it.</i>
- Okay. I will.

72
00:04:17.757 --> 00:04:21.470
[exhales deeply] Okay. Hazenator.
come here.

73
00:04:23.597 --> 00:04:24.598
Okay.

74
00:04:27.142 --> 00:04:28.935
- Mom. I gotta go…
- Okay.

75
00:04:28.936 --> 00:04:30.394
…before Prem's dad starts honking.

76
00:04:30.395 --> 00:04:31.479
Okay.

77
00:04:31.480 --> 00:04:33.065
[Hazel panting]

78
00:04:34.608 --> 00:04:35.692
[exhales deeply]

79
00:04:38.362 --> 00:04:40.364
[tense music playing]

80
00:04:43.742 --> 00:04:45.619
[keypad beeping]

81
00:04:46.453 --> 00:04:48.872
[line ringing]

82
00:04:56.964 --> 00:04:58.674
[operator] <i>911. what's your emergency?</i>

83
00:05:00.467 --> 00:05:02.176
[tense music builds]

84
00:05:02.177 --> 00:05:04.679
<i>Hello? 911. what's your emergency?</i>

85
00:05:04.680 --> 00:05:07.057
[upbeat music playing]

86
00:05:22.698 --> 00:05:24.991
[muffled dialogue]

87
00:05:24.992 --> 00:05:26.285
[Geri speaks indistinctly]

88
00:05:26.952 --> 00:05:28.537
Can you please talk to me?

89
00:05:29.580 --> 00:05:30.581
[muffled. echoing] Paula?

90
00:05:31.957 --> 00:05:34.959
Paula. Are you-you okay?

91
00:05:34.960 --> 00:05:36.878
No. I mean. he was dead.

92
00:05:36.879 --> 00:05:39.463
I… [stammers] …There was blood everywhere.

93
00:05:39.464 --> 00:05:41.633
And then all of a sudden he's gone.

94
00:05:43.552 --> 00:05:44.844
[Geri] Shit. his phone is locked.

95
00:05:44.845 --> 00:05:46.805
How does a body just disappear?

96
00:05:47.931 --> 00:05:49.558
[knocks on door]

97
00:05:54.688 --> 00:05:55.897
Hey. [sighs]

98
00:05:55.898 --> 00:05:57.773
Security camera's busted
at that store you went to.

99
00:05:57.774 --> 00:05:58.859
so that's a dead end.

100
00:05:59.651 --> 00:06:02.486
[sighs] I did get
incredibly expensive Takis though.

101
00:06:02.487 --> 00:06:03.905
I feel like I'm going insane.

102
00:06:03.906 --> 00:06:06.200
I feel like I'm actually going insane.

103
00:06:07.784 --> 00:06:09.035
This is real.

104
00:06:09.036 --> 00:06:11.038
This tells us that it really happened.

105
00:06:11.622 --> 00:06:12.623
[Paula] Yeah.

106
00:06:18.337 --> 00:06:21.881
You said you had his phone number. right?
The number on this phone.

107
00:06:21.882 --> 00:06:23.091
Yeah.

108
00:06:23.759 --> 00:06:24.968
[grunts]

109
00:06:26.303 --> 00:06:27.387
[sniffles]

110
00:06:32.893 --> 00:06:34.561
Okay. put it in. Put it in.

111
00:06:35.521 --> 00:06:36.730
- [Rudy] Okay.
- Let's go.

112
00:06:44.404 --> 00:06:45.571
- Again.
- Okay.

113
00:06:45.572 --> 00:06:47.991
- Sorry.
- [Paula smacks lips. groans]

114
00:06:52.204 --> 00:06:53.622
Okay. that's actually pretty smart.

115
00:06:56.750 --> 00:06:58.377
[Paula] Oh. the code is this.

116
00:06:59.670 --> 00:07:01.338
No fucking way.

117
00:07:04.591 --> 00:07:05.717
Hmm. Okay.

118
00:07:12.599 --> 00:07:13.975
- [Geri] John Smith?
- [Paula] Yeah.

119
00:07:13.976 --> 00:07:15.978
That sounds super real
and not made up at all.

120
00:07:16.728 --> 00:07:18.563
[Geri] John.

121
00:07:18.564 --> 00:07:20.941
[Paula] All of these are going
to the same address.

122
00:07:26.113 --> 00:07:27.197
That's. like. 30 minutes away.

123
00:07:28.407 --> 00:07:31.826
We should go check it out.

124
00:07:31.827 --> 00:07:35.371
[scoffs] Or maybe we don't visit
a murderer's house. right?

125
00:07:35.372 --> 00:07:37.874
- Dead murderer.
- [Rudy] Disappeared dead murderer.

126
00:07:37.875 --> 00:07:39.876
Exactly.
So there'll be zero murderers there.

127
00:07:39.877 --> 00:07:42.753
If we can get inside. maybe we can
figure out something about who he was.

128
00:07:42.754 --> 00:07:46.966
or-or something that shows us
that he killed Trevor. and not me.

129
00:07:46.967 --> 00:07:48.718
Come on. you guys. I'm freaking out.

130
00:07:48.719 --> 00:07:50.345
Can you please go with me tomorrow?

131
00:07:51.180 --> 00:07:52.556
Please. guys.

132
00:07:53.140 --> 00:07:55.057
- [Rudy sighs]
- Yeah. 100%.

133
00:07:55.058 --> 00:07:57.435
[Paula] Okay. I have this
stupid fundraiser thing. but right after.

134
00:07:57.436 --> 00:07:59.145
[stammers] One hundred per…

135
00:07:59.146 --> 00:08:02.231
Okay. maybe. like. can we just focus
on the phone first. right?

136
00:08:02.232 --> 00:08:05.068
Like there's gotta be more stuff on there
if we can just get past the lock screen.

137
00:08:06.195 --> 00:08:07.570
We'll do both.

138
00:08:07.571 --> 00:08:08.739
I might know someone.

139
00:08:22.336 --> 00:08:23.962
- Hey. Drew.
- Hey.

140
00:08:27.257 --> 00:08:28.633
Should I be hydrating too?

141
00:08:28.634 --> 00:08:30.885
Just got back from DC
on an Air Force transport

142
00:08:30.886 --> 00:08:32.720
- and my back is. like. pretzel-ed.
- Mmm.

143
00:08:32.721 --> 00:08:34.765
[inhales deeply] But I could be cajoled.

144
00:08:35.515 --> 00:08:37.099
Uh. no. I'm not here for that.

145
00:08:37.100 --> 00:08:39.519
Um. I need this cracked.

146
00:08:39.520 --> 00:08:42.312
That's super illegal. <i>madame</i>.

147
00:08:42.313 --> 00:08:43.315
[Geri] Uh-huh.

148
00:08:43.899 --> 00:08:45.775
I know you have someone
who does this shit for you.

149
00:08:45.776 --> 00:08:46.692
[sighs]

150
00:08:46.693 --> 00:08:47.818
I'm working on something

151
00:08:47.819 --> 00:08:50.906
and it's a big story
that I think Suzie would be into.

152
00:08:51.657 --> 00:08:53.283
This phone could blow
the whole thing open.

153
00:08:54.201 --> 00:08:56.160
It's a burner. Not gonna have much.

154
00:08:56.161 --> 00:08:58.079
I don't need much. I just need in.

155
00:08:58.080 --> 00:09:01.041
Wow. a fact-checker coming after my job.

156
00:09:01.583 --> 00:09:03.668
I thought it was just gonna be
me versus the machines.

157
00:09:03.669 --> 00:09:04.794
Are you gonna help me or not?

158
00:09:04.795 --> 00:09:06.922
- How good is the story?
- It's fucking great.

159
00:09:18.517 --> 00:09:22.187
First off. you gotta make sure
the battery is out always.

160
00:09:22.771 --> 00:09:24.397
If it's got juice in it.
it can be tracked.

161
00:09:24.398 --> 00:09:26.483
- And I'm guessing you don't want that.
- No.

162
00:09:27.067 --> 00:09:28.943
Okay. I'll get this to my guy.

163
00:09:28.944 --> 00:09:30.445
I have been incredibly helpful.

164
00:09:31.530 --> 00:09:33.698
- And kinda manly.
- Mmm.

165
00:09:33.699 --> 00:09:36.284
Sure you don't wanna… [clicks tongue]

166
00:09:36.285 --> 00:09:38.119
No. Thanks. Drew. [chuckles]

167
00:09:38.120 --> 00:09:40.830
What? Why? Is…
You're… [stammers] …seeing someone else?

168
00:09:40.831 --> 00:09:44.458
What? No. I just. um.
wanna keep things professional.

169
00:09:44.459 --> 00:09:46.294
Okay. well. then pay me.

170
00:09:46.295 --> 00:09:47.629
[door opens. closes]

171
00:09:50.674 --> 00:09:52.676
[whimsical. eerie music playing]

172
00:10:06.607 --> 00:10:07.608
[inhales sharply]

173
00:10:16.158 --> 00:10:18.075
So. he just flaked?

174
00:10:18.076 --> 00:10:19.619
[Scott] <i>I-I don't know what to say.</i>

175
00:10:19.620 --> 00:10:21.829
<i>Frank's always been
my most reliable investigator.</i>

176
00:10:21.830 --> 00:10:23.165
<i>but I can't get a hold of him.</i>

177
00:10:23.832 --> 00:10:25.541
<i>Want me to hire a new PI?</i>

178
00:10:25.542 --> 00:10:27.960
Um. I don't know. We'll talk it over.

179
00:10:27.961 --> 00:10:29.254
Okay. thank you.

180
00:10:29.838 --> 00:10:31.715
Jesus Christ.
do you really think we need one?

181
00:10:32.591 --> 00:10:33.674
You don't?

182
00:10:33.675 --> 00:10:34.676
No. I don't.

183
00:10:35.385 --> 00:10:37.970
You freaked out yesterday
when you heard she has a new boyfriend.

184
00:10:37.971 --> 00:10:39.055
Y-Yeah… [sighs]

185
00:10:39.056 --> 00:10:42.141
- Is there something I should know?
- No. there's nothing you need to know.

186
00:10:42.142 --> 00:10:45.395
I just don't think we need
to ruin her life in order to win.

187
00:10:46.146 --> 00:10:47.688
But we do have to win.

188
00:10:47.689 --> 00:10:50.108
- Agreed.
- And to win. you have to be ruthless.

189
00:10:50.734 --> 00:10:51.901
Merciless.

190
00:10:51.902 --> 00:10:53.069
Okay. I can't do that.

191
00:10:53.070 --> 00:10:55.863
- This is the mother of my child. Mal.
- I know. I know.

192
00:10:55.864 --> 00:10:57.782
You know? There's a line for me.
and this is the line.

193
00:10:57.783 --> 00:11:01.410
I get it. and I love you for it.

194
00:11:01.411 --> 00:11:04.205
And it's why I have to be merciless
for the both of us.

195
00:11:04.206 --> 00:11:06.624
["Feels Like A Different Thing" playing]

196
00:11:06.625 --> 00:11:08.334
Let's go. mama owls!

197
00:11:08.335 --> 00:11:10.127
[cheering]

198
00:11:10.128 --> 00:11:13.882
[instructor] Raise those arms
to raise that money!

199
00:11:14.466 --> 00:11:15.925
Let it out!

200
00:11:15.926 --> 00:11:17.928
["Feels Like A Different Thing" continues]

201
00:11:20.055 --> 00:11:21.055
[groans]

202
00:11:21.056 --> 00:11:22.724
[music distorts]

203
00:11:26.854 --> 00:11:28.856
[distorted panting]

204
00:11:33.569 --> 00:11:34.819
- [yells]
- [yells]

205
00:11:34.820 --> 00:11:35.821
[panting]

206
00:11:38.365 --> 00:11:39.324
[laughs]

207
00:11:41.827 --> 00:11:44.705
["Feels Like A Different Thing"
continues. distorted]

208
00:11:48.125 --> 00:11:49.917
- Help!
- Wait. shit.

209
00:11:49.918 --> 00:11:52.044
Paula. Paula. Paula.

210
00:11:52.045 --> 00:11:54.630
- You're bleeding.
- What? Oh!

211
00:11:54.631 --> 00:11:56.424
[chuckles] Oh. my God.

212
00:11:56.425 --> 00:12:01.512
I had a. uh… a dermaplane. uh.
accident this morning.

213
00:12:01.513 --> 00:12:03.181
Yeah. It's okay.

214
00:12:03.182 --> 00:12:05.141
Um. are you. uh…

215
00:12:05.142 --> 00:12:06.810
Have you written that referral letter?

216
00:12:07.811 --> 00:12:08.895
I'm sorry. what?

217
00:12:08.896 --> 00:12:11.063
You know. the-the-the custody letter.

218
00:12:11.064 --> 00:12:14.317
I really need to. um…
to-to get them to my lawyer.

219
00:12:14.318 --> 00:12:15.693
- Yeah. I'll send it right over.
- Yeah.

220
00:12:15.694 --> 00:12:18.487
- Oh. good. Okay.
- Um. are you good though?

221
00:12:18.488 --> 00:12:20.323
Yeah. Me? I'm great.

222
00:12:20.324 --> 00:12:21.574
I'm so great.

223
00:12:21.575 --> 00:12:23.285
This is so fun.

224
00:12:23.785 --> 00:12:25.746
Oh. my God. what a great event.

225
00:12:26.914 --> 00:12:28.665
You go. girl. [chuckles]

226
00:12:32.252 --> 00:12:33.794
[Gonzales] I don't know.

227
00:12:33.795 --> 00:12:35.338
- [Baxter] You don't know?
- [Gonzales] Mm-mmm.

228
00:12:35.339 --> 00:12:36.547
What more do you need?

229
00:12:36.548 --> 00:12:40.218
Her prints are on the nail gun
that nailed the victim to the floor.

230
00:12:40.219 --> 00:12:42.845
not to mention the nail
in his leg and the walls.

231
00:12:42.846 --> 00:12:45.681
She was… [imitates gun]
…spraying nails like Rambo.

232
00:12:45.682 --> 00:12:47.266
He wasn't killed by a nail.

233
00:12:47.267 --> 00:12:48.809
Are you secretly in love with her?

234
00:12:48.810 --> 00:12:49.811
I don't understand.

235
00:12:50.479 --> 00:12:53.940
He was killed with expanding insulation.
Her prints aren't even on the can.

236
00:12:53.941 --> 00:12:55.942
Why would she wipe the can
and not the nail gun?

237
00:12:55.943 --> 00:12:59.529
I don't know. Murderers do stupid shit
like commit murder.

238
00:12:59.530 --> 00:13:01.781
Ah. The numbers add up.
but the sum is wrong.

239
00:13:01.782 --> 00:13:03.366
Stop talking like Yoda.

240
00:13:03.367 --> 00:13:06.160
She's not even strong enough to do this.

241
00:13:06.161 --> 00:13:08.329
She's not even strong enough
to choke Trevor out.

242
00:13:08.330 --> 00:13:11.207
She's not barbell strong.
but she could be Pilates strong.

243
00:13:11.208 --> 00:13:13.626
She's just a little piece of chicken.

244
00:13:13.627 --> 00:13:15.795
Her prints are everywhere.

245
00:13:15.796 --> 00:13:18.422
She has motive.
Lieutenant wants us to close the case.

246
